{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"24355-little-ant-s-big-plan","title":"Little Ant's Big Plan","description":"This is a story about a little ant with a big plan, and how his love for reading saved the day.","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"2","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Candice  Dingwall"],"illustrators":["Steven McKimmie"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Book Dash","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/24355-little-ant-s-big-plan"},"cover":{"card":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86165/size3/cdaec4ae12cc711034c3eefcfd214d40.jpg","large":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86165/size6/cdaec4ae12cc711034c3eefcfd214d40.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86056/size6/b47b95753c5d5271dbfcb6c4e0273ad3.jpg","text":"Little Ant loved to read. Little Ant was often teased. \n“Ants don’t read. Ants must feed. Ants collect the food they need.”","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86057/size6/e7de0135ac803d84cf405e65a7f1728f.jpg","text":"Little Ant would read all day, he’d read and read the day away.","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86058/size6/8c8c3d989a1687923a9904f933c22ef0.jpg","text":"The other ants took what they\nfound to store for winter underground.","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86059/size6/f2bdd6669c15969d14b47d67c5e2262c.jpg","text":"His mum and dad got really mad, and Little Ant felt really bad.","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86060/size6/d9216f42c73dfb38c9fe61a5e97ae199.jpg","text":"In autumn when the leaves fall down.","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86061/size6/76a0a24cc2b3bb73698c77d4447586b0.jpg","text":"The ants must keep \nfood underground.","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86062/size6/32336b2464bc46a93fa014197adcc42b.jpg","text":"The Queen wants food to fill the store, so all the ants must work some more.","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86063/size6/7f5dd25435aff92978495b01aac578a3.jpg","text":"Little Ant begins to shout about a place he read about. \n“A restaurant is what we need, a place where people go to feed. It says so in the books I read.”","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86064/size6/d8e1be2edba278285e49e28da9a4c2f6.jpg","text":"The ants go marching one by one. They march into the setting sun.","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86065/size6/fce831fcf94df19ce2793abc15e1be84.jpg","text":"11/19","words":null},{"n":11,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86066/size6/e9ad748e924ab11cd8b4d3b2efdfadcd.jpg","text":"And Little Ant said \n“Hey, there’s one!”","words":null},{"n":12,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86068/size6/32ad37c765c845332a72d24cc8b1d95d.jpg","text":"The ants go marching one by one, carrying a burger, carrying a bun.","words":null},{"n":13,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86069/size6/0fbe7a24eb91ab5a6ec4f8d00019a658.jpg","text":"When they return the Queen is glad. \nThe stores are full. \nThey cheer like mad.","words":null},{"n":14,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86070/size6/ed526e15becb1d3e471f67f5a682a4fd.jpg","text":"15/19","words":null},{"n":15,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86071/size6/130f8714b5d6ef9ba69cf9096ef26c00.jpg","text":"Ant gets hugs from mum and dad.","words":null},{"n":16,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86072/size6/385ba02f1b629dc62bdab4ff631a268b.jpg","text":"His baby sister takes his hand “Now I think I understand.” \n“The way you love to read a book … Makes me want to take a\nlook.”","words":null},{"n":17,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86073/size6/2e6f1f926631d1bed7cbc7d1603ba929.jpg","text":"18/19","words":null},{"n":18,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/86074/size6/bae5a6e01bc5f0c325cd4320bf42bfd4.jpg","text":"19/19","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":18,"words":207}}